<L>__{interior collins house continuous}
<A>__{the lights are low. christine sits on the floor, sorting through a box containing artifacts of affection: class projects made by walter, trees and houses and clay dogs; a heart shaped card mother's day card, hand made, with i love you, mommy carefully printed on the front. she runs her finger over it, tracing the impression left by his pencil. she starts to cry, and a tear falls onto the pencil drawing. she frantically dabs at it, trying to preserve it from distortion...then sets it down and covers her face, weeping.}
